{"messages": [{"type": "human", "data": {"content": "Is it safe to travel to Colombia right now?", "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "human", "name": null, "id": null, "example": false}}, {"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "", "additional_kwargs": {"tool_calls": [{"id": "call_WDJe7mH2vUfMTnSdHfCTxyGK", "function": {"arguments": "{"country":"Colombia"}", "name": "get_travel_advisory"}, "type": "function"}], "refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 19, "prompt_tokens": 1932, "total_tokens": 1951, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": 0, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 0, "rejected_prediction_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 1792}}, "model_name": "gpt-4o-2024-08-06", "system_fingerprint": "fp_395c203642", "finish_reason": "tool_calls", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "run--019e147d-d90d-7170-8bf4-8736437e7b27-0", "example": false, "tool_calls": [{"name": "get_travel_advisory", "args": {"country": "Colombia"}, "id": "call_WDJe7mH2vUfMTnSdHfCTxyGK", "type": "tool_call"}], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 1932, "output_tokens": 19, "total_tokens": 1951, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 1792}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}}, {"type": "tool", "data": {"content": "{
  "country": "Colombia",
  "us_advisory": "Prepare for your trip toColombiaby reviewing theStateDepartmentTravelAdvisory, entry and exit requirements, local laws, andU.S. embassy tips. ReconsidertraveltoColombiadue to crime, terrorism, civil unrest, kidnapping, and natural disasters. Some areas have an increased risk. Read the entireTravelAdvisory.DoNotTravelto: Arauca, Cauca (excluding Popayán), Valle del Cauca (excluding Cali) and Norte de Santanderdepartmentsdue to crime and terrorism. Within 10km/5mi of theColombia-Venezuela border region due to crime ... Colombiatrip planning got harder on March 31,2026, when theU.S.StateDepartmentreissued itsLevel3advisoryand explicitly folded natural disasters into a risk picture that already included crime, terrorism, unrest, and kidnapping. That does not make allColombiaitineraries unworkable, but it does change how travelers should judge side trips, overland routing, and recovery plans outside ... TheU.S.DepartmentofStateissued aLevel3traveladvisoryforColombiaon Tuesday, urging Americans to reconsider traveling there due to widespread crime, terrorism, civil unrest, kidnapping ... TheUSStateDepartment'sLevel3advisoryisnota barrier totravel— it is a framework for informed decision-making. Business professionals who approachColombiawith structured protocols — verified transport, pre-arranged hotel pickups, domestic flights between cities, and disciplined nightlife awareness — will find Bogotá ...",
  "uk_advisory": "2 weeks ago -FCDO travel advice for Colombia. Includes safety and security, insurance, entry requirements and legal differences. March 17, 2026 -Before traveling to Colombia, run a free Colombia travel warning check to see the current safety score, active travel advisory warnings and entry requirements. Our live Colombia travel advisory warning is updated daily from the US State Department, UK FCDO, Australian Smartraveller and Canadian government. December 29, 2025 -FCDO travel advice for Colombia. Includes safety and security, insurance, entry requirements and legal differences. March 24, 2026 -You should think about your need to travel to this country, territory or region based on family or business requirements, knowledge of or familiarity with the region, and other factors. 2 weeks ago -The FCDO advises against all but essential travel to parts of Colombia, it has warned."
}", "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": null, "id": null, "tool_call_id": "call_WDJe7mH2vUfMTnSdHfCTxyGK", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}, {"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Colombia is a country of vibrant culture and stunning landscapes, but it's important to be aware of the current travel advisories. The U.S. Department of State has issued a Level 3 advisory for Colombia, urging travelers to reconsider their plans due to crime, terrorism, civil unrest, kidnapping, and natural disasters. Certain areas, such as Arauca, Cauca (excluding Popayán), Valle del Cauca (excluding Cali), and Norte de Santander, are particularly risky.

The UK Foreign, Commonwealth & Development Office (FCDO) also advises against all but essential travel to certain parts of Colombia. They recommend considering your need to travel based on personal or business requirements and familiarity with the region.

If you decide to travel, it's crucial to plan carefully. Use verified transport, arrange hotel pickups in advance, and consider domestic flights between cities for safer travel. Always stay informed and cautious, especially when exploring areas outside major cities like Bogotá.

If you have specific plans or areas in Colombia you're interested in, feel free to share, and I can provide more tailored advice or recommendations.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 218, "prompt_tokens": 2477, "total_tokens": 2695, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": 0, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 0, "rejected_prediction_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 1920}}, "model_name": "gpt-4o-2024-08-06", "system_fingerprint": "fp_395c203642", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "run--019e147d-ecab-7791-943d-413be336ca60-0", "example": false, "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2477, "output_tokens": 218, "total_tokens": 2695, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 1920}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}}]}

